            <title>[GROOVY-7243] @Delegate does not honor &quot;includes&quot; on properties - all properties are delegated</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7243</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The @Delegate documentation states that the &quot;includes&quot; element is a&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;List of method and/or property names to include when delegating.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the &quot;includes&quot; does not affect the delegating of property getters and setters.  All properties from the delegate are currently delegated regardless of their inclusion in the &quot;includes&quot; element.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expected: When the includes element is provided on the @Delegate attribute, only the properties specified are delegated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
